{"word":"Jehoshaphat","slug":"jehoshaphat","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Jehoshaphat</b> - <b>(a)</b> David's Recorder<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=8&verse=16'>2Sa 8:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=20&verse=24'>2Sa 20:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=4&verse=3'>1Ki 4:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=18&verse=15'>1Ch 18:15</a><p/><b>(b)</b> King of Judah, son of Asa<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=15&verse=24'>1Ki 15:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=22&verse=41'>1Ki 22:41</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=8&verse=16'>2Ki 8:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=17&verse=1'>2Ch 17:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=18&verse=1'>2Ch 18:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=19&verse=1'>2Ch 19:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=20&verse=1'>2Ch 20:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=21&verse=1'>2Ch 21:1</a><p/>--Summary of his life<p/>One of the best kings of Judah<p/>Had a godly father<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=14&verse=2'>2Ch 14:2</a><p/>Inaugurated a system of religious instruction for the people<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=17&verse=7'>2Ch 17:7-9</a><p/>Commanded the Judges to be just<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=19&verse=6'>2Ch 19:6-9</a><p/>When surrounding nations attacked him he trusted in the Lord and gained<p/>a great victory<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=20&verse=1'>2Ch 20:1-37</a><p/>He manifested weakness in forming alliances with wicked kings<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=22&verse=1'>1Ki 22:1-36</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=3&verse=4'>2Ki 3:4-27</a>"}]}